N2  - The article focuses on commentary concerning an article on socioevolutionary theory and it's potential in contributing to management theory. It talks about Abraham Maslow and his hierarchy of needs as well as Maslow's study in primatology. It examines Maslow's dominance studies and mentions that Maslow's explanations and conclusions are not considered valid after 60 years of added research. Another comment states that Maslow stated in a seminal article that there wasn't a reason to start with animals in a study of human motivation. A third comment states that Maslow's theory of human motivation isn't directly derived from evolutionary theory, but that there is consistency with it.
AB  - The article focuses on commentary concerning an article on socioevolutionary theory and it's potential in contributing to management theory. It talks about Abraham Maslow and his hierarchy of needs as well as Maslow's study in primatology. It examines Maslow's dominance studies and mentions that Maslow's explanations and conclusions are not considered valid after 60 years of added research. Another comment states that Maslow stated in a seminal article that there wasn't a reason to start with animals in a study of human motivation. A third comment states that Maslow's theory of human motivation isn't directly derived from evolutionary theory, but that there is consistency with it.
